# Tests and README stay current

When you **change behavior, add features, fix bugs, or touch tooling/CI/deploy paths**, also:

1. **Tests** — Update or add unit/integration tests for the affected projects (e.g. `tests/*.test`, `frontend/**/*.test.ts`, `frontend/**/*.test.tsx`). Run `make build` or the relevant `dotnet test` / `npm run ci` before finishing.
2. **README.md** — If setup steps, project layout, scripts, env vars, badges, or deploy instructions change, update the root README in the same change set so newcomers and CI expectations match reality.

Do not leave “docs-only-in-chat” guidance when the repo should reflect it.
